Third-party notices
===================

This file records attribution obligations for third-party code, per the
parser-provenance rules in architecture.md §10.

- Native parsers written from reverse-engineered facts ("reference"
  provenance) carry no notice and are not listed here.
- Any parser ported from iLEAPP or another project ("port" provenance)
  must add the upstream copyright line and license text below, and mark
  its source header `// provenance: port of <module> — see
  THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES`.
- iLEAPP itself runs as a separate sidecar process (downloaded from its
  official GitHub releases at first use); it is not linked into or
  distributed within this binary.

